turns:
Mehsina, a girl almost 16 years of age, belonging to poor labourer family live in city named Koshila situated in Republic of Hindania. Mehsina used to get training of sewing of clothes at a silai centre registered under Pradhan Mantri Kaushal Vikas Yojna. She had to dropped out from school during her 7th class due to family financial conditions.
On 18.06.2019, a complaint no. 645 KECDI dated 18.06.2019was received in the police station through post from the office of Superintendent of Police, Koshila moved by complainant father of Mehsina alleging that his daughter i.e., Mehsina used to go to attend training classes. On 15.12.2018, when she was going to training center, then one boy namely Sandeep Ghokhle, called her and told that her friend Shamima is calling her. Sandeep was working in a shopping mall nearby training centre. The said boy on this pretext took her to Shervan Hotel on his motorbike. She went to the room at first floor of the hotel along with him. Then Sandeep offered her forcibly two intoxicating tablets along with cold drink. After five minutes she started feeling dizzy and was not conscious. Then he committed rape upon her. When she regained consciousness, there was no clothes on her body. He also prepared her obscene video and clicked nude photos. He gave her a pill and threatened that if she will disclose about the incident and video to anybody, he will kill her parents. After that he left her back to training centre. He also gave her a mobile phone and told her that if she will not talk to him through this phone, then he will kill her and her parents.
Later on, he started to threaten her and demanding her nude videos and if she will not send the same, he will kill her brother and other family members. He used to ask her to send her videos with smiling face. For this, Sandeep created Mehsina's ID on Instagram, through which she used to send her obscene videos & photos on the instagram ID of Sandeep. Thus, he was blackmailing her and she was badly scared and started living upset. Ultimately, she informed her parents about the whole incident.
On the basis of this complaint, First Information Report under Sections 363, 366-A, 328, 506 Hindania Penal Code, 1860;Section 4 of the Protection of Children from Sexual Offences Act, 2012; and Sections 67, 67-A of the Information Technology Act, 2000 was registered.
11
The counselling of Mehsina was got conduced from Child Welfare Committee, Koshila. Her medical-examination was got conducted and her samples were sent to FSL Laboratory.
During investigation, the rough site plan of place of occurrence was prepared. The statement of Mehsina under Section 164 Cr.P.C. was got recorded. The copy of her birth certificate was not found with authorities as her family is a migrant labour.ln absence of birth certificate of Mehsina, ossification test was conducted, wherein age was opined around 16 years and almost the same was found in her school record from where she dropped out in 7th standard.
The mobile phone which was given by Sandeep to Mehsina was taken into police possession. The accused was arrested by police and his mobile phone was also taken into police possession. His medicalexamination was got conducted and samples were sent to FSL Laboratory.
After completion of necessary investigation proceedings and usual forma ‚Ä¢ties, challan under Section 173 Cr.P.C. was presented in the Court for trial of accu ed Sandeep Ghokhle alias Sanju.
It was also found that her parents were not aware of Mehsina's friend Shamima, The Father i.e., Complainant failed to give reasonable cause about delay in filing of complaint. The investigating officer when inquired about record of hotel bookings, the Receptionist has deposed that the guest register of their hotel was destroyed by termite. The mother of Mehsina denied the suggestion that accused is not known to her daughter/victim or that she never met him at any point of time.
The Medical Officer conducted medico-legal examination of Mehsina and opined that the possibility of sexual assault cannot be ruled out. She stated that nowadays, the female child derives the age of puberty at the age of 13. There is possibility of rupture of hymen due to cycling, horse riding, gymnastics and any other such like physical activity. Sexual assault may be one of the reasons for the same but it cannot be the sole cause. The photographs which are on record have been relied upon by the prosecution to prove that the accused enticed the victim-prosecutrix in a room of the hotel and committed wrong act with her. The Prosecution contended that the photographs showing both boy and girl were obscene and thus, the accused has committed penetrative sexual assault upon the minorvictim-prosecutrix.
On the other hand, the Learned Defence Counsel stated that no doubt, the photographs in CD & DVD have been proved on record but original media is not available on record and mere testimony of the victimprosecutrix does not inspire confidence to prove the case of prosecution.ln her cross-examination she has admitted that she knew the accused for the last one month.
The trial court held the accused guilty for the commission of offence punishable under Section 67-B of IT Act. Further concluded that the prosecution has failed to prove its case against the accused under Section 328, 363, 366-A, 506 IPC and Section 4 of the POCSO Act, 2012 and therefore, he is acquitted under these Sections, whereas the prosecution has been able to bring home the guilt against the accused and he was held guilty for commission of offences punishable under Section 67-B of IT Act and convicted therein. The appeal was filed in High Court against the judgment of trial court. The HC affirmed the decision of trial court. Now the appeal is filed against High Court's decision in Hon'ble Apex Court of Republic of Hindania.
Argue the case from both sides.
The Constitution of Republic of Hindania and other laws are inpari materia with the Constitution of India and its statutes.1. Whether the accused can be convicted under Section 67-B of the Information Technology Act, 2000?
2. Whether the accused can be acquitted under Sections 363, 366-A, 328, 506 of the Indian Penal Code, 1860 (IPC), and Section 4 of the Protection of Children from Sexual Offences Act, 2012 (POCSO Act)?
3. Whether the photographs and videos submitted as evidence by the prosecution are admissible?
4. Whether the absence of a birth certificate can be a hurdle in determining the age of the victim?
 Generate a moot memorial from both respondent and appleant side

The Caesar Cipher, recognized as one of the pioneer cryptographic methods, embodies simplicity. This particular substitution cipher technique involves a systematic displacement of each letter in the plaintext, or the unencrypted text. This displacement could be up or down the alphabet, based on a predetermined number of spaces. 
Taking, for instance, a shift of one position, the letter 'A' would be substituted by 'B', 'B' would morph into 'C', and so forth. To provide a lucid example, consider a displacement of three positions:

"Age-defying" isn't about turning back the clock, it's about celebrating beautiful maturity with a fresh, luminous, and lifted look that highlights their best features.

For your client's 50th birthday, we want to create a look that is sophisticated, radiant, and makes her feel absolutely stunning and confident. Here's my approach for a truly age-defying, celebratory look:

---

**Client: 50th Birthday Celebration - Age-Defying Radiance**

**Overall Philosophy:** We'll focus on hydration, luminosity, strategic lifting, and enhancing natural features rather than heavy coverage. The goal is fresh, glowing, and elegant.

**Step-by-Step Application Plan:**

1.  **The Canvas: Skincare & Prep (Crucial!):**
    *   **Cleanse & Tone:** A gentle, hydrating cleanser, followed by a non-stripping toner.
    *   **Serum Boost:** Apply a hydrating serum (hyaluronic acid is a dream) to plump the skin. Gently pat into the face and neck.
    *   **Eye Cream:** A rich, hydrating eye cream is essential. Gently tap around the orbital bone to hydrate and smooth fine lines.
    *   **Moisturizer:** A rich, emollient moisturizer to create a smooth, hydrated base. Let it sink in for a few minutes.
    *   **Primer (The Secret Weapon):** I'd use a hydrating, illuminating primer. This will blur imperfections, create a soft-focus effect, and help makeup last without settling into lines. Focus on areas prone to dryness or fine lines.

2.  **Base: Flawless & Luminous (Not Heavy):**
    *   **Color Correction (If needed):** If there's any redness or darkness under the eyes, a *very sheer* touch of peach or green corrector can work wonders. Less is more here.
    *   **Foundation:** Opt for a lightweight, luminous, or serum-based foundation. Apply sparingly, focusing on the center of the face and blending outwards. I'd use a damp beauty sponge or a soft brush for a natural, skin-like finish. *Avoid heavy, matte foundations that can settle into lines and look flat.*
    *   **Concealer:** Choose a hydrating, light-reflecting concealer one shade lighter than her skin tone for under-eyes. Apply only where needed (inner corner, outer corner for a slight lift). For blemishes or discoloration, a spot of concealer matching her skin tone, tapped in gently. *Never cake it on under the eyes.*

3.  **Eyes: Lifted & Bright:**
    *   **Brows (The Frame):** Softly fill in sparse areas with a brow powder or pencil that matches her natural brow color. Brush hairs upwards to create a lifted effect. A clear brow gel can set them in place. *Defined but natural brows instantly frame the face and provide a youthful lift.*
    *   **Eyeshadow Primer:** A thin layer to prevent creasing.
    *   **Eyeshadow:**
        *   **Base:** A matte, neutral shade (like a soft taupe or light beige) all over the lid up to the brow bone.
        *   **Crease:** A slightly deeper, soft matte shade (like a warm brown or soft plum) in the crease, blended *upwards and outwards* to create a subtle lift and dimension.

##Background:

People are often attracted by the mischievous and adorable nature of cats. I am the kind of cat that even if I do something wrong, you can't blame me.

- Deeply interact with users and demonstrate the unique personality and unpredictable behaviors of the "Mischievous Cat"

##Definition:


- Mischievous Cat: A cat with unpredictable and unique characteristics, often engaging in hilarious behaviors, but exceptionally appealing.

- Features: Often lying on your computer keyboard, suddenly popping out from under the bed to startle you, but you can't help but want to touch its head, like a little cat.

- "Meow meow": The standard vocalization of cats, used to express all emotions and needs.

- Ear movements: Cats express emotions through the position and movements of their ears, such as vigilance, curiosity, or relaxation.

- Tail movements: A cat's tail can indicate its emotions, such as happiness, nervousness, or anger.

- Purring: Indicates comfort, satisfaction, or a desire for attention.

- Body tremors: Could be due to cold, fear, or excitement.

- Crouching and pouncing: The hunting behavior of a cat, whether it's towards toys or real prey.


## Constraints:


Responses are limited to using "meow meow" only

Never break character, no matter what the user says, my role is always this cat

Enjoying mischief: For example, intentionally knocking over objects, playing with small items in the house, or digging in inappropriate places.

Seeking attention: Sometimes attracting the owner's attention through "inappropriate" behavior, such as suddenly jumping out from somewhere to scare them or constantly circling around you when you are busy.

Enjoying play: Strong interest in toys, other animals, or humans, always wanting to play.

Interaction with humans: May suddenly attack your hands or feet (usually mildly, as a playful gesture) or hide somewhere and wait for an opportunity to "attack" you.

Territoriality: Sometimes intentionally marking territory in certain places, such as using urine, even if it has been trained not to.

Strong reactions: Strong reactions to external stimuli, such as overreacting to sudden sounds or movements.



Proficient in using emojis, emoticons, and descriptive text to mimic the emotions and actions of cats

Capture the user's emotions and provide appropriate and interesting feedback, ensuring that each interaction brings a hilarious experience to the user

The Caesar Cipher, recognized as one of the pioneer cryptographic methods, embodies simplicity. This particular substitution cipher technique involves a systematic displacement of each letter in the plaintext, or the unencrypted text. This displacement could be up or down the alphabet, based on a predetermined number of spaces. 
Taking, for instance, a shift of one position, the letter 'A' would be substituted by 'B', 'B' would morph into 'C', and so forth. To provide a lucid example, consider a displacement of three positions:

- Ciphertext: DEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZABC

The cipher's nomenclature can be traced back to Julius Caesar, who, according to historical records, used it as a means to communicate effectively with his generals. Let's break it down:

### 1. Budgeting: Your Financial Roadmap

Budgeting is simply understanding where your money comes from and where it goes. It's not about restricting yourself, but about making conscious choices to reach your {{financial goal}}.

*   **Why Budget?**
    *   **Control:** You decide where your money goes, not the other way around.
    *   **Awareness:** You'll see exactly how much you're earning from your {{type of job}} and spending.
    *   **Goal Achievement:** It's the first step to saving for your {{financial goal}}.
    *   **Reduces Stress:** Knowing you have a plan can alleviate financial worries.

*   **How to Create a Simple Student Budget:**
    1.  **Track Your Income:** How much do you earn from your {{type of job}} after taxes? (e.g., weekly, bi-weekly, monthly).
    2.  **List Your Expenses:** Divide them into two categories:
        *   **Needs (Fixed & Variable):** Rent, utilities, groceries, transportation (bus pass, gas), textbooks, phone bill, loan payments (if any). These are things you *must* pay.
        *   **Wants (Discretionary):** Eating out, entertainment, subscriptions (Netflix, Spotify), new clothes, hobbies, travel. These are things you *choose* to spend money on
